00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:29.180
products. Let's take a look at why that is
[BEEP] stupid. We're going to focus on the

00:00:29.180 --> 00:00:33.380
elements of environmentalism that you most
often hear about. Water, paper - meaning trees

00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:38.810
- and CO2 emissions. Let's start with water.
Now one of the common water saving tips that

00:00:38.810 --> 00:00:43.579
you hear is to get a water efficient shower
head. The typical shower head emits 5 gallons

00:00:43.579 --> 00:00:48.920
per minute. Most water efficient shower heads
emit 2.5 gallons per minute. Say that you

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:55.329
take 10 minute showers every day, you're going
to save 9,125 gallons every year. If you take

00:00:55.329 --> 00:01:02.489
a 15 minute shower every day, you're going
to save 13,687.5 gallons every year. The average

00:01:02.489 --> 00:01:09.030
US citizen eats 185 pounds of meat every year,
and 62.4 pounds of beef. So every year the

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:14.509
average American is using 156,000 gallons
of water for their beef consumption alone.

00:01:14.509 --> 00:01:21.880
If you didn't eat any meat for an entire year,
conservatively, you'd be saving 339,900 gallons.

00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:27.679
The average American also eats 632 pounds
of dairy. Every pound of dairy takes approximately

00:01:27.679 --> 00:01:33.200
600 gallons of water. So if you stopped eating
dairy for entire year, you would save 379,200

00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:37.850
gallons. Now here's the real testament. If
you went an entire year without eating any

00:01:37.850 --> 00:01:43.950
meat or dairy, you would be saving 719,100
gallons of water for that year. That's the

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:49.149
same amount of water as if you didn't shower
at all for 53 years if you took a 15 minute

00:01:49.149 --> 00:01:54.149
shower, or 79 years if you took 10 minute
showers. So what's really making the best

00:01:54.149 --> 00:01:59.389
environmental impact as far as water is concerned?
So maybe a full year with no meat or dairy

00:01:59.389 --> 00:02:03.420
is a little too much for you to handle right
now. What about not eating 1 pound of beef?

00:02:03.420 --> 00:02:08.590
You would be saving the same amount of water
as if you didn't shower for 100 showers. That's

00:02:08.590 --> 00:02:13.640
3 1/2 months of not showering, just for 1
pound of beef. I hope you're starting to see

00:02:13.640 --> 00:02:18.780
how huge the impact of diet is on the environment.
Now it's time for paper. What you most often

00:02:18.780 --> 00:02:23.170
hear for helping the environment, is to start
going paperless. And also to recycle whatever

00:02:23.170 --> 00:02:29.980
paper you do use. On average, a person uses
between 5 and 8.51, 40 foot trees every year.

00:02:29.980 --> 00:02:35.730
And if you recycled 1 ton of paper, that's
2,000 pounds, you'll be saving about 17 trees.

00:02:35.730 --> 00:02:39.760
And now for dietary impact. I'm only going
to use the data for beef right now, because

00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:43.879
it is the meat that's had the most environmental
impact studies done. To produce 1 pound of

00:02:43.879 --> 00:02:48.459
beef, it takes approximately 55ft.Â² of rain
