pounds of toilet paper every year. Let's say,

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:31.640
dear Americans, that you went an entire year
without using any toilet paper. You would

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:38.719
be saving a measly 0.425 trees. Now for CO2.
The animal products industry is the largest

00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:45.469
sole contributor to climate change, and is
responsible for emitting 2,964 million tons

00:03:45.469 --> 00:03:50.540
of CO2 every year. Now let's compare the CO2
emissions of the average car to that of the

00:03:50.540 --> 00:03:54.890
meat dairy and egg industries. When people
talk about saving CO2, you always hear about

00:03:54.890 --> 00:04:00.640
hybrid cars. The average passenger car is
going to emit 5.1 tons of CO2 per year. Now

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:05.160
